tion in their own image, arguing that they were the country's most faithful supporters of freedom and liberty and that their church had birthed American independence. Making Catholic America offers a new interpretation of American life in the Gilded Age and Progressive Era, demonstrating the surprising success of an often-embattled religious group in securing for itself a place in the national community and in profoundly altering what it meant to be an American in the modern world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCatholicszUnited StatesxHistoryy19th century. 0aCatholicszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 4aETHNIC STUDIES. 4aReligious Studies. 7aHISTORY / United States / 19th Century.2bisacsh  aCatholics and American nationalism, Catholic-Protestant relations, religion andAmerican politics, religion in the Gilded Age, religion in the Progressive Era, religion and American empire, history of religion in the United States, Catholicism and American identity.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075183308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishz978311131913108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501771002?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501771002423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501771002/original  a978-3-11-075183-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131913-1  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishb2023  a9